  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Turashoboye: To protect and empower women, men, girls and boysliving in vulnerable communitiesRCBIF2</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The HPP project will continue to build resilience by addressing acute humanitarian needs using distribution of nutritional kits/ NFIs based on assessments, including food security and use of VSLA/ IGA, and strengthening community capacity to support peace at the local level and to prevent and respond to GBV with a focus on building community resilience and conflict transformation capacity, building on experience from the previous project phases as well as the increased focus on from violence to peace, Building Peace and resilience</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Vulnerable, conflict-affected women, men, girls and boys in Makamba and Rumonge Provinces, Burundi, lead more secure, dignified lives and have increased resilience to ongoing and future shocks and stresses</narrative>
  </description>
